2 HOUSE BILL 1111
1 2–205.
2 (a) There is a Class 3 winery license.
3 (b) A license holder may:
4 (1) establish and operate a plant for fermenting and bottling wine at the
5 location described in the license;
6 (2) import bulk wine from the holder of a nonresident dealer’s permit;
7 (3) ACQUIRE BULK WINE FROM THE HOLDER OF A CLASS 4 LIMITED
8 WINERY LICENSE;
9 (4) sell and deliver wine to:
10 (i) a holder of a wholesaler’s license;
11 (ii) a holder of a permit that is authorized to acquire wine; and
12 (iii) a person outside the State that is authorized to acquire wine;
13 [(4)] (5) subject to subsection (c) of this section, sell at retail wine made
14 at the plant from products grown in the State to an individual participating in a guided
15 tour of the plant; and
16 [(5)] (6) serve, at no charge, not more than 6 ounces of wine made at the
17 plant to an individual who has attained the legal drinking age and is participating in a
18 guided tour of the plant.
19 (c) An individual may purchase wine under subsection [(b)(4)] (B)(5) of this
20 section if the individual has attained the legal drinking age.
21 (d) The license holder shall report to the Executive Director annually on a form
22 provided by the Executive Director on:
23 (1) the amount of alcoholic beverages produced under the license;
24 (2) the amount of alcoholic beverages sold for off–premises consumption;
25 and
26 (3) the amount of alcoholic beverages served for on–premises consumption.
27 (e) Except as otherwise provided by law, the license holder may not sell alcoholic
28 beverages for off–premises consumption to a person who intends to resell the alcoholic
29 beverages.

HOUSE BILL 1111 3
1 (f) The annual license fee:
2 (1) shall be determined by the Executive Director; and
3 (2) may not exceed $750.
4 2–206.
5 (b) There is a Class 4 limited winery license.
6 (c) (1) A license holder may:
7 (i) subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, from available
8 Maryland agricultural products:
9 1. ferment and bottle wine; and
10 2. distill and bottle pomace brandy; [and]
11 (ii) sell and deliver the wine and pomace brandy to:
12 1. a holder of a wholesaler’s license;
13 2. a holder of a permit that is authorized to acquire wine or
14 pomace brandy; or
15 3. a person outside the State that is authorized to acquire
16 wine or pomace brandy; AND
17 (III) SELL AND DELIVER BULK WINE TO THE HOLDER OF A CLASS
18 3 WINERY LICENSE.
19 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
20 1, 2026.

